Attached are five files:
 cf.js: Provides the autocomplete functionality, the editor resizing,
and change-tracking functionality. Should be loaded into the outer
document using a script tag
 parsecf.js: Provides the parser. Should be passed in the parserfile
option when initializing CodeMirror.
 cfsyntax.js: This is the current version of the 'syntax' file that
can later be updated to provide support for new constructs. This one
was created by Eystein. The idea is that some kind of server-side
script will generate this in production. Also should be passed through
the parserfile option.
 cfcolors.css Provides color definitions for the various syntax elements.
 resize.png Resize picture.

You'll need to use a version of CodeMirror no older than last week
(which, right now, means the development snapshot at [1], since no
official releases have been done this week), and initialize it (using
either CodeMirror.fromTextArea or new CodeMirror, see the manual) with
an options argument containing at least these settings:

{
    parserfile: ["cfsyntax.js", "parsecf.js"],
    stylesheet: "css/cfcolors.css", // you may have to adjust the path
    path: "js/", // again, may need adjustment
    lineNumbers: true,
    styleNumbers: styleLineNum,
    initCallback: function(e){initComplete(e); initResize(e); initChangeTracker(e);},
    onChange: contentChanged,
    continuousScanning: 500
  }

In the html head, the following should be included

    <style type="text/css">
      .completions {
        border: 1px solid black;
        z-index: 10;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .completions select {
        outline: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
        border: 0;
        background-color: white;
        font-family: monospace;
        font-size: 80%;
      }
      .CodeMirror-wrapping {
        border-top: 1px solid #911;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #911;
        padding: 3px;
      }
      .CodeMirror-line-numbers {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        padding-top: 3px;
        margin-right: .4em;
        width: 2.2em;
        color: #aaa;
        text-align: right;
        padding-right: .3em;
        font-size: 10pt;
        font-family: monospace;
      }
    </style>


[1]: marijn.haverbeke.nl/codemirror/codemirror-latest.zip
